# AWS VPC, EC2 & Security Groups Notes

## 1. VPC Setup Steps
- Create a VPC with CIDR block (e.g., 10.0.0.0/16)
- Create Public and Private Subnets
- Attach Internet Gateway to VPC
- Configure Route Tables
- Associate Subnets with Route Tables

---

## 2. EC2 Deployment Steps
- Launch EC2 Instance (Amazon Linux / Ubuntu)
- Select VPC and Subnet
- Assign Security Group
- Create or use Key Pair (.pem file)
- Connect using SSH:
  ssh -i key.pem ec2-user@public-ip

---

## 3. Security Groups Configuration
- Allow SSH (Port 22) → My IP only
- Allow HTTP (Port 80) → 0.0.0.0/0
- Allow HTTPS (Port 443) → 0.0.0.0/0
- Restrict all unnecessary inbound traffic
- Use least privilege principle

---

## 4. Key Concepts Learned
- VPC = Virtual Private Cloud (isolated network)
- Subnets = Division of VPC
- Internet Gateway = Internet access
- Security Groups = Firewall rules
